---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getLangFromUrl, useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<head>
  <title>BoycottWithAI — Civil resistance against manipulation, environmental exploitation and speciesism</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Practical tools for non-violent actions: OSINT, ethical AI, disruptive resources against fascism, disinformation, climate crisis. Campaigns, data and resources for global justice." />
  <meta name="keywords" content="civil resistance UK, non-violent actions, against fascism 2025, environmental justice, animal rights, OSINT ethics, AI transparency, disinformation fight, climate crisis, speciesism, mutualism, antifascism digital" />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://boycottwithai.com/en/" />
</head>

<Base>
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="left">
      <h1>Civil resistance: act now against fascism, exploitation and rearmament</h1>
      <p class="lead">Digital tools and practical resources to expose manipulation, rearmament presented as “security”, climate crisis and repression. Defend public services, the environment and democratic accountability.</p>
      <p class="muted">2025: rising military budgets framed as national security while welfare and services are cut. Document violations of EU law and build evidence for infringement procedures.</p>
      <div class="cta">
        <a class="button" href={`/${lang}/actions/`}>Disruptive Actions</a>
        <a class="secondary" href={`/${lang}/tools/`}>OSINT Tools</a>
        <a class="secondary" href={`/${lang}/resources/`}>Download Resources</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px; border-left:4px solid #c33;">
        <h3>Report EU Violations — Italy / France / Germany</h3>
        <p class="muted">We prioritise documented breaches of EU environmental law, wastewater treatment, waste management and public procurement. Build airtight dossiers to initiate or support infringement procedures.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:6px"><strong>Key EU references:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2008/50/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directive 2008/50/EC — Ambient air quality</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/1991/271/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directive 91/271/EEC — Urban wastewater treatment</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2008/98/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directive 2008/98/EC — Waste framework</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2014/24/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directive 2014/24/EU — Public procurement</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2022/2555/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directive (EU) 2022/2555 (NIS2) — Cybersecurity / critical infra</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">What to collect: official monitoring datasets, certified stations, administrative acts, contracts, geotagged photos, chronological evidence.</p>
        <div style="margin-top:8px">
          <a class="secondary" href="/templates/infringement-report-en.md" download aria-label="Download infringement report template (EN)">Download template (EN)</a>
          <a class="secondary" href="/downloads/resources/priority-infractions-it.md" style="margin-left:8px">Priority infractions (IT)</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section style="margin-top:28px">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Why now?</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Manipulation:</strong> Controlled media spread hate and lies.</li>
          <li><strong>Exploitation:</strong> Capital uses state for profit, ignoring poor and nature.</li>
          <li><strong>Repression:</strong> Rights cuts, animal culls, social control.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Key Actions</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/actions/`}>10 Disruptive Actions</a> (speculation maps, satire, crowdfund)</li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/tools/`}>OSINT & AI Monitoring</a> (GDELT, Bellingcat, sentiment)</li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/resources/`}>Templates & Data</a> (petitions, briefings, dashboards)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Safety</h4>
        <p class="muted">Anonymity and privacy: use Tor, minimal data, secure reporting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:28px">
    <h2>Global Issues and Regional Specifics</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Rearmament and Militarization</h4>
        <p class="muted">Global military spending +12% in 10 years (SIPRI). Governments justify with fear narratives for economic incentives.</p>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Demand defense budget transparency, audit contracts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Environmental Crisis</h4>
        <p class="muted">Warming >1.5°C, 70% biodiversity loss (IPCC/UN). Private profit causes deforestation, pollution.</p>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Just energy transition, end fossil subsidies, protect areas.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Speciesism and Animal Exploitation</h4>
        <p class="muted">Wolf culls in Italy +200% since 2020, hunting, factory farming. Animal life sacrificed for profit.</p>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Hunting bans, predator protection, ethical veganism, animal rights.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
      <h4>UK-Specific Criticisms 2025</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Environment:</strong> Deforestation in Scotland, Thames pollution, energy crisis post-Brexit.</li>
        <li><strong>Animals:</strong> Fox hunting resurgence, factory farming, wildlife trafficking.</li>
        <li><strong>Social:</strong> Austerity cuts, poverty rise, repression of protests.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Concrete Actions:</strong> Sign petitions against hunting, monitor environmental bills, join local campaigns.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:28px">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Immediate Resources</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Download <a href="/downloads/templates/petition-en.txt">petition</a> or <a href="/downloads/templates/mp-email-en.txt">email MPs</a></li>
        <li>View <a href={`/${lang}/dashboard/`}>data visualizations</a> on military spending and welfare</li>
        <li>Access <a href={`/${lang}/resources/`}>detailed technical resources</a> for scraping, AI, video</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:28px">
    <div class="card" style="background:rgba(200,50,100,0.05);border-left:4px solid #c832">
      <h4>Epstein Files: Power Networks Exposed</h4>
      <p class="muted"><strong>60,000+ pages officially released (2025).</strong> Institutional failures, money flows, complicity networks revealed.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Choose your approach:</strong></p>
      <ul style="padding-left:20px;margin-top:8px">
        <li><strong>Quick search:</strong> <a href="https://jmail.world" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JMail.world</a> — searchable email database from exposed networks</li>
        <li><strong>Deep analysis:</strong> <a href={`/${lang}/tools/#epstein`}>Download complete methodology</a> — reproducible workflow to acquire, process, and analyze 60,000+ documents yourself with Python OCR, SQLite FTS5 database, entity extraction, co-occurrence analysis, and timeline reconstruction</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:0.9em;color:#666"><strong>Why autonomy matters:</strong> Build your own searchable database. Verify findings. Control the analysis. Updated sources, tools, and step-by-step guides included.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top:28px;border-top:2px solid var(--accent);padding-top:28px">
    <h2>Build with Open Tools. Don't Buy Corporate Platforms.</h2>
    <div class="card" style="background:rgba(20,184,166,0.05)">
      <p style="font-weight:600">Corporate digital services are decaying. LLMs and open-source ecosystems are replacing proprietary platforms at every layer.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Why it matters for us:</strong></p>
      <ul style="padding-left:20px;margin-top:8px">
        <li><strong>Data sovereignty:</strong> Open-source tools run on your infrastructure—your data stays yours.</li>
        <li><strong>No vendor lock-in:</strong> Export all data anytime. Avoid corporate ToS traps.</li>
        <li><strong>Lower cost:</strong> Free alternatives to Salesforce, Zoom, Slack, AWS are production-ready.</li>
        <li><strong>Community control:</strong> Projects evolve with users, not shareholders. Transparency is built in.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Start here:</strong></p>
      <ul style="padding-left:20px;margin-top:8px">
        <li>Replace corporate email → NextCloud / ProtonMail</li>
        <li>Replace corporate video → Jitsi Meet / Element</li>
        <li>Replace corporate chat → Mattermost / Rocketchat</li>
        <li>Replace corporate AI → Ollama (run GPT-sized models locally)</li>
        <li>Replace corporate analytics → Metabase / Superset</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:18px"><a href={`/${lang}/tools/`}><strong>See full list of 5,000+ free public APIs and open-source alternatives →</strong></a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
